  "prompt": "I want to start selling digital art I made in Photoshop. How can I make sure the colors come out how they look on screen & high resolution?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to ensure high-quality digital art prints:\n\n1. Color Management\n- Use color calibration tools for your monitor\n- Work in Adobe RGB or sRGB color space\n- Calibrate your monitor with a hardware calibration device\n\n2. Resolution\n- Create artwork at least 300 DPI for high-quality prints\n- Use larger canvas sizes (e.g., 3000x4000 pixels)\n- Save in high-quality file formats like TIFF or PNG\n\n3. Print Preparation\n- Convert colors to CMYK for professional printing\n- Use soft proofing in Photoshop to preview print colors\n- Consider getting test prints from different services\n\n4. Recommended Printing Services\n- Printful\n- Society6\n- RedBubble\n- Minted\n- Zazzle\n\n5. Selling Platforms\n- Etsy\n- DeviantArt\n- Redbubble\n- Society6\n- Your own website\n\n6. Additional Tips\n- Use ICC color profiles\n- Invest in a good monitor with wide color gamut\n- Consider professional printing services for fine art prints",
